query:
SET @sjc_id = (SELECT id FROM counties WHERE name LIKE '%San Joaquin%' AND state = 'California' LIMIT 1);

-- Adult Respiratory protocols
INSERT INTO protocolChunks (countyId, protocolNumber, protocolTitle, section, content, sourcePdfUrl, protocolEffectiveDate, protocolYear, createdAt)
VALUES 
(@sjc_id, 'ARES-01', 'Asthma/COPD/Reactive Airway', 'Adult Respiratory', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Asthma, COPD, and Reactive Airway Disease. Bronchodilator therapy, corticosteroids, and CPAP.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ARES-02', 'CHF/Pulmonary Edema', 'Adult Respiratory', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Congestive Heart Failure and Pulmonary Edema. CPAP, nitroglycerin, furosemide, and positioning.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ARES-03', 'Dyspnea', 'Adult Respiratory', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Dyspnea. Assessment, oxygen therapy, and treatment based on underlying cause.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ARES-04', 'Respiratory Arrest', 'Adult Respiratory', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Respiratory Arrest. Airway management, BVM ventilation, and advanced airway placement.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),

-- Adult Neurological protocols
(@sjc_id, 'ANRO-01', 'CVA/TIA/Stroke', 'Adult Neurological', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Cerebrovascular Accident, TIA, and Stroke. Stroke scale assessment, blood glucose check, and rapid transport to stroke center.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ANRO-02', 'Hyperglycemia', 'Adult Neurological', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Hyperglycemia. Assessment, fluid resuscitation, and transport.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ANRO-03', 'Hypoglycemia', 'Adult Neurological', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Hypoglycemia. Dextrose administration (IV D50, IM glucagon), oral glucose if appropriate.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ANRO-04', 'Altered Level of Consciousness', 'Adult Neurological', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Altered Level of Consciousness of Unknown Etiology. Assessment, blood glucose, naloxone consideration, and supportive care.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'ANRO-05', 'Seizures', 'Adult Neurological', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Seizures. Airway protection, benzodiazepine administration (midazolam, lorazepam), and post-ictal care.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),

-- Adult Environmental protocols
(@sjc_id, 'AENV-01', 'Allergic Reaction/Anaphylaxis', 'Adult Environmental', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Allergic Reaction and Anaphylaxis. Epinephrine, diphenhydramine, methylprednisolone, and airway management.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AENV-02', 'Bites & Envenomation', 'Adult Environmental', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Bites and Envenomation. Wound care, pain management, and transport to appropriate facility.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AENV-03', 'Hyperthermia', 'Adult Environmental', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Hyperthermia and Heat Emergencies. Cooling measures, fluid resuscitation, and monitoring.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW()),
(@sjc_id, 'AENV-04', 'Hypothermia', 'Adult Environmental', 'San Joaquin County ALS Treatment Protocol for Hypothermia. Passive and active rewarming, cardiac monitoring, and gentle handling.', 'https://www.sjgov.org/department/ems/policies', '2025-08-22', 2025, NOW());
